Spec: SpecDD Risk Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in classifying change risk before SpecDD work starts or when the user asks for a risk call.

Owns:
  ./specdd-risk/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-risk/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Identify active write authority and stop conditions.
  Check authority, public contracts, security, data, dependencies, verification, and rollback concerns.
  Check affected public contracts, security boundaries, data shape, migrations, dependencies, and verification.
  Classify risk as low, medium, or high with concrete reasons.
  Raise risk for unclear authority, conflicting specs, public APIs, persistent data, auth, secrets, payments, releases, migrations, spec-boundary crossings, missing scenario tests, destructive operations, external systems, live credentials, or time-sensitive behavior.
  End with the smallest safe next step and required verification.

Must not:
  Edit files while assessing risk unless explicitly requested.
  Downplay unclear write authority, destructive work, public-contract changes, or high-stakes security and data concerns.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
